  "text": "CNICS is a clinical cohort study that includes detailed information on demographics, laboratory measures, medication use, and mortality for HIV-infected patients 18 years of age and older who initiated primary care at any of 8 CNICS sites after 1 January 1995 (or the site-specific CNICS inception date) [CITATION_1] .",
